title: Get a criminal record check to become a driving instructor

heading_context: Get a criminal record check to become a driving instructor
chunks.html_content:
Get a criminal record check if you’re applying to become an approved driving instructor (ADI) for the first time.

You cannot use one you have already - you must get a new one.
chunks.plain_content:

Get a criminal record check if you’re applying to become an approved driving instructor (ADI) for the first time.
You cannot use one you have already - you must get a new one.

heading_context: Get a criminal record check to become a driving instructor
chunks.html_content: There’s a different service to get a criminal record check to renew your ADI registration.
chunks.plain_content:
Get a criminal record check to become a driving instructor
There’s a different service to get a criminal record check to renew your ADI registration.

heading_context: Get a criminal record check to become a driving instructor
chunks.html_content:
Check if you can become a driving instructor before you apply.

When you’ve finished the online application, you must give proof of your identity.

You can do this at a Post Office offering the ‘CRB and ID verification service’.

You’ll need to take a printed page from your online application with barcodes on it and 3 original forms of ID (not copies). These can be:

  • your passport
  • your driving licence
  • a utility bill that’s less than 3 months old
  • a bank statement that’s less than 3 months old

The service costs £8.22.
